Data Scientist		Bomoda		Greater New York City Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong>Data Science Engineer</strong> </p><p></p><p>Bomoda’s vision is to create a transparent view of the consumer in the world’s most complex retail markets. We are seeking a talented data scientist to help expand our intelligence platform which provides insights into the retail tourism market to better understand the impact of tourism on global product demand.  </p><p></p><p><strong>What to expect:</strong> </p><p>As a data science engineer at Bomoda, you would be directly involved with the product team including computer scientists and data analysts, eliciting information from multiple data platforms and using that data to identify relevant and actionable trends and/or concepts. The product goal is to understand consumer behavior abroad to better detect market conditions as well as the general perception of brands by the retail tourist. </p><p></p><p><strong>What we’re looking for:</strong> </p><p>The ideal candidate would have a Mandarin literacy, as the data sets currently used are exclusively Chinese. Also critical would be knowledge of at least one general-purpose programming language (preferably but not necessarily Python, Ruby, or Scala) and familiarity with BASH, as well as basic experience using Hadoop and SQL. Experience with data mining, statistical modeling, and machine-learning techniques are also a must. </p><p></p><p>If this sounds like you, contact us!</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Bomoda helps leading brands connect the dots. Using a proprietary mix of data science and human curation, we offer a new level of transparency into what drives customer behavior around the world. We unite divergent data sources to improve customer understanding, market strategy and business execution.<br /><br />That’s why we created the 2015 Bomoda China Blueprint series. We wanted to build the most comprehensive data set on Chinese consumers’ global purchasing behavior. We wanted to connect brands’ marketing activities directly to business outcomes. We wanted to provide a blueprint for brand executives on resource allocation and marketing execution.<br /><br />And, most importantly, we wanted this blueprint to empower leading brands, analysts, investors and entrepreneurs to fundamentally re-imagine their true potential with the Chinese consumer.</div>